create new venv with pyenv (version python 3.7)

1.
sudo apt-get update
sudo apt-get install -y build-essential libssl-dev zlib1g-dev libbz2-dev libreadline-dev libsqlite3-dev wget curl llvm libncurses5-dev libncursesw5-dev xz-utils tk-dev libffi-dev liblzma-dev

2. Instalar o pyenv
curl https://pyenv.run | bash

3. Reinicie o terminal ou execute o seguinte comando para carregar as novas
source ~/.bashrc

4. Instalar o Python 3.7 usando o pyenv:
pyenv install 3.7.12

5. Criar um ambiente virtual com Python 3.7 usando venv
cd ~/python-projects
virtualenv --python=$(which python3.7) venv2

6. Ativar o ambiente virtual
source venv2/bin/activate

